# Privacy Policy — CEChecker

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

CEChecker is a Chrome extension that scans web pages for circular economy terminology. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

CEChecker does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.

All scanning happens locally in your browser tab. The extension reads the visible text of the current page, matches it against a built-in glossary, and displays results in the popup. Nothing is saved or sent anywhere.

## Data Storage

CEChecker does not use any browser storage APIs. No data persists between sessions.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party.

## Permissions

- **scripting** — used to inject the scanner and highlighter functions into the active tab
- **activeTab** — grants temporary access to the current tab when the popup is opened, without requiring broad host permissions

## Changes to This Policy

This policy may be updated occasionally. The latest version will always be available at this URL.

## Contact

For questions about this extension, open an issue on the GitHub repository.
